How Do You Connect Two VPCs?

How can two VPCs communicate with each other?

What are the different ways to connect two VPCs?

How do you enable private connectivity between two VPCs?
=======

anser is single for all questions:


 âœ… Method 1: VPC Peering (Most Common)

 ðŸ”¹ What it is

A private, direct connection between two VPCs using private IPs.

 ðŸ”¹ When to use

 Same cloud (AWSâ†”AWS, Azureâ†”Azure, GCPâ†”GCP)
 Low latency
 Simple architecture

 ðŸ”¹ How it works (Simple Flow)

```
VPC-A (10.0.0.0/16)
   â†• Peering
VPC-B (10.1.0.0/16)
```

 ðŸ”¹ Requirements

 No overlapping CIDR
 Route tables updated on both sides
 Security Groups allow traffic

 ðŸ”¹ Linux Admin Role

 Test connectivity using private IPs

ping
traceroute
ssh

 Debug routing/firewall issues



 âœ… Method 2: VPN (Site-to-Site VPN)

 ðŸ”¹ What it is

An encrypted tunnel over the internet between two VPCs.

 ðŸ”¹ When to use

 Cross-cloud (AWS â†” Azure)
 Temporary or hybrid setup
 Security needed over public internet

 ðŸ”¹ How it works


VPC-A aws
  â†• VPN Tunnel (Encrypted)
VPC-B gcp


 ðŸ”¹ Linux Admin Role

 Verify routes to remote CIDR
 Debug tunnel connectivity
 Check firewall rules



 âœ… Method 3: Transit Gateway / Hub Network (Enterprise)

 ðŸ”¹ What it is

A central hub that connects multiple VPCs.

 ðŸ”¹ When to use

 Many VPCs
 Large enterprise architecture

 ðŸ”¹ Example

```
VPC-A \
VPC-B  Transit Gateway  On-Prem
VPC-C /
```

 ðŸ”¹ Linux Admin Role

 Rarely configures
 Mostly troubleshoots routing



 âŒ What You CANNOT Use 

 Internet Gateway âŒ
 NAT Gateway âŒ
 Public IP communication âŒ



