Interview One-Line Answer

> Two VPCs can be connected using VPC peering, a site-to-site VPN, or a transit gateway depending on scale and security requirements.





 Who does this: Linux Admin or Network Engineer?

 ðŸ‘‰ Answer: BOTH â€” but with different responsibilities



 ðŸ”¹ Network Engineer Role (Primary Owner)

Network engineers design and create the connectivity.

They do:

 Create VPC / VNet
 Configure VPC Peering / VPN
 Set CIDR blocks
 Configure Route Tables
 Setup Transit Gateway
 Design network architecture

ðŸ‘‰ They BUILD the network



 ðŸ”¹ Linux Admin Role (Operational Owner)

Linux admins use, validate, and troubleshoot the network.

They do:

 Verify server connectivity
 Test access using private IPs
 Debug routing issues from OS side
-----
ip route
ping
traceroute
-----
 Check Security Groups / NSG
 Check OS firewall
 Report issues to network team

ðŸ‘‰ They RUN on the network



